  "local_port": 38450,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there any way to insert image/picture in nedit text editor?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, the standard version of NEdit (NEdit - a UNIX text editor) does not support inserting images directly into the text editor. NEdit is primarily designed for editing plain text files and lacks the capability to embed or display images within the editing area.\n\nHowever, there are a few potential workarounds or alternatives you might consider:\n\n1. **External Image Viewer**: You can open an image in a separate image viewer application while working in NEdit. This way, you can visually reference the image while editing text.\n\n2. **Using ASCII Art**: If you need a visual representation within the text itself, you can use ASCII art to create simple drawings using text characters. There are online tools available that can convert images to ASCII art.\n\n3. **Enhanced NEdit Versions or Plugins**: While standard NEdit doesn't support images, it's possible that some enhanced versions or plugins might offer this functionality. You would need to search for community-developed versions or extensions specifically designed for this purpose.\n\n4. **Alternative Editors**: If inserting images is a critical feature for your workflow, consider using a more feature-rich text editor or an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) that supports image insertion, such as Visual Studio Code, Sublime Text, or others.\n\n5. **Markdown or HTML**: If your text file supports Markdown or HTML, you can include image references in your document. For example, using Markdown:\n   ```\n   ![Image Description](path/to/your/image.jpg)\n   ```\n   Or using HTML:\n   ```html\n   <img src=\"path/to/your/image.jpg\" alt=\"Image Description\">\n   ```\n   These will not display the image in NEdit, but the file can be rendered with the image in a compatible viewer or web browser.\n\nWhile these options don't allow for direct image insertion in NEdit, they provide alternative ways to work with images in conjunction with your text editing.",
